PN,35305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1779369077
OL,3,CMeet the man who can't remember his
OL,4,Cown wedding day
OL,6,FThe charity says more than 600,000
OL,7,Fpeople in the UK have epilepsy, and
OL,8,Fmany of them face some form of memory
OL,9,Floss.
OL,11,FMs Smith said: "It is very common.
OL,12,FThat's why we wanted to highlight this
OL,13,Fin National Epilepsy Week.
OL,15,F"We surveyed a number of our community
OL,16,Fand over half were saying it wasn't
OL,17,Fjust memory loss on a daily basis but
OL,18,Falso memory loss of key life moments.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1779369077
OL,3,CMeet the man who can't remember his
OL,4,Cown wedding day
OL,6,F"Epilepsy is an electrical malfunction
OL,7,Fthat is going on in the brain, so if
OL,8,Fyou think about it in that way it's
OL,9,Fnot surprising that memories do get
OL,10,Flost amongst that.
OL,12,F"This isn't just about seizures, but
OL,13,Fit's also about the medication people
OL,14,Fneed to live with, which can also
OL,15,Fcause memory loss."
OL,17,FFor Bob, the ramifications of his
OL,18,Fepilepsy and memory loss have been
OL,19,Fharder to deal with than he ever
OL,20,Fanticipated.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1779369077
OL,3,CMeet the man who can't remember his
OL,4,Cown wedding day
OL,6,FHe said: "I never expected the trauma
OL,7,Fas well that goes with it. And then, I
OL,8,Fsuffer from anxiety.
OL,10,F"But to deal with someone's memory
OL,11,Floss is quite strange, because you
OL,12,Fthen are dealing with something where
OL,13,Fyou think, does that person remember
OL,14,Fme? I noticed that particularly when I
OL,15,Fwas first diagnosed."
OL,17,FBob and Jan have come up with coping
OL,18,Fmechanisms to help deal with his
OL,19,Fmemory loss, and the pair say that, if
OL,20,Fanything, the condition has brought
OL,21,Fthem closer together.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1779369077
OL,3,CMeet the man who can't remember his
OL,4,Cown wedding day
OL,6,FBob said: "Jan is a list maker. I do
OL,7,Fthings and I make sure we keep doing
OL,8,Fthem, and we build up sort of new
OL,9,Fmemories.
OL,11,F"And if some of those are a bit fuzzy,
OL,12,Fwe just talk. We talk and talk and we
OL,13,Fwalk along beaches.
OL,15,F"We definitely are closer."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
